Let me out of here!

289
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:22,730
(EXCLAIMS)

290
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:27,151
Linda!

291
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:28,945
Maybe l should. . .

292
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,738
No, no.
Give it a chance.

293
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:37,620
(GULPS)

294
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:46,087
Hello?

295
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:50,675
l come in peace.

296
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:57,849
BLU: Whoa.
She's beautiful.

297
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:04,981
What were they
talking about?
She's like an angel.

298
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:10,570
An angel who's
getting really close...

299
00:17:11,989 --> 00:17:13,531
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

300
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:15,450
(MUFFLED)

301
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:17,827
You're standing
on my throat.

302
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,620
Oh, you're
an American.

303
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:21,622
(CLEARING THROAT) Thanks.

304
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:23,666
l need my throat for
talking. So, thank you.

305
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:25,376
You look like me.

306
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:27,420
(HIGH-PITCHED) Hi.

307
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:29,172
(CLEARING THROAT)
Hi, my name is Blu.

308
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:31,549
Like the cheese
with the mold on it.

309
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:33,009
You know, that
smells really bad.

310
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:35,344
That's stupid.
Stupid, stupid, stupid.

311
00:17:35,512 --> 00:17:37,889
Come on.
We don't have much time.

312
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:39,182
(EXCLAIMING)

313
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,767
Wait, wait, wait.

314
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:54,155
Are you ready?
For what? Oh ! Oh.

315
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:56,240
Wow. Okay.

316
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:59,827
Confidence.
Crazy love-hawk.

317
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:02,205
All right.

318
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:03,956
Whoa, what
are you doing?

319
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:05,750
What? What you
wanted me to.

320
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:08,836
But just for argument's sake,
what are you doing?

321
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:11,422
l am trying to escape.

322
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:14,175
Yeah, escape, that's
where l was going

323
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:15,551
with that thing l just did.

324
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:19,097
Wait, wait.
Did you actually think
we were going to kiss?

325
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:20,556
No! it’s not what you think.
We just met.

326
00:18:20,724 --> 00:18:21,766
Oh, my.

327
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:23,893
l think they need
a little help.

328
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:25,770
l know how
my feathers look,

329
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:27,396
but l am not
that kind of bird.

330
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:29,440
Say you, say me

331
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:32,026
Okay, l had nothing
to do with that.

332
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:35,196
But, you have to admit
it's actually a pretty
good song.

333
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:38,449
Naturally

334
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:39,951
Yeah, sing it, Lionel.

335
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:41,035
(BLU EXCLAIMING)

336
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,834
Wow. That was fast.

337
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:51,254
Lionel Richie
works every time.

338
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:54,006
We should probably give
them some privacy.

339
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:03,349
I’m not so sure
l should leave Blu
here alone.

340
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:04,892
No, don't worry.

341
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:07,311
Sylvio will keep an eye
on them all night.

342
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:14,068
Besides, he's got Jewel.

343
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,571
(BLU SQUAWKING)

344
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:21,951
Help me!

345
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:26,664
(RJ CHATTERING ON RADIO)

346
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:29,375
This is the final
countdown to Carnaval!

347
00:19:29,459 --> 00:19:30,918
Let's samba!

348
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,587
(SAMBA MUSIC PLAYING)

349
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:36,799
(WHOOPS)

350
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:42,180
(METAL CLATTERING)

351
00:19:57,404 --> 00:19:58,779
Oh. . .

352
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:03,159
Come here,
poor little birdie.

353
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:06,954
it’s okay, l got you.

354
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:08,497
l got you.

355
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,000
(MUFFLED)

356
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:28,267
(METAL CLINKING)

357
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:29,810
(MOANING)

358
00:20:31,647 --> 00:20:33,022
Excuse me.

359
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:36,150
Please, l am
trying to sleep.

360
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:40,738
I’m sorry, sleepy-head,
I’m trying to escape.

361
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:44,533
Escape? Why?
This cage is awesome.

362
00:20:44,701 --> 00:20:46,327
This. . . (LAUGHS)

363
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,037
Oh, what was l thinking?

364
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:51,457
l wouldn't expect
a pet to understand.

365
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,876
Pet? Did you just
call me a pet?

366
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:56,003
For the record,
l am not a pet.

367
00:20:56,171 --> 00:20:57,546
l am a companion.

368
00:20:57,631 --> 00:20:59,048
And you know what?
Do whatever you want

369
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:01,133
'cause tomorrow morning,
Linda will come for me

370
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:02,969
and this whole nightmare
will be over.

371
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:04,303
Incredible!

372
00:21:04,388 --> 00:21:07,807
You would rather be
with a human than
with your own kind.

373
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:10,601
Well, that human
has given me love
and affection

374
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:11,894
for the past 1 5 years

375
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:15,231
whereas my own kind
try to strangle me
after 1 5 seconds.

376
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:18,109
Yeah, well, because of them,
I’ve lost everything.

377
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:19,777
You can't trust them.
(DOOR OPENING)

378
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:20,945
BLU: Of course. . .

379
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,405
you can trust humans.

380
00:21:22,489 --> 00:21:23,864
(JEWEL GRUNTS)

381
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:26,033
Jewel? Jewel?

382
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,077
Hi, there.

383
00:21:38,922 --> 00:21:40,631
TULIO: It was nice of you
to join me for dinner.

384
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:42,883
l often eat alone.

385
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:45,177
Because, of course,
my work.

386
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:48,556
l thought l was the bird
nut until l met you.

387
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:49,807
Yes, right.

388
00:21:50,058 --> 00:21:51,559
Do you have
a favorite bird?

389
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:55,604
Well, obviously,
I’m a blue macaw
kind of gal.

390
00:21:55,772 --> 00:21:58,357
That makes sense.
They are very
handsome birds.

391
00:21:58,525 --> 00:22:00,985
Actually, it's the brains
I’m more attracted to.

392
00:22:01,278 --> 00:22:03,821
I’m not so impressed
by fancy feathers.

393
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:05,614
l know exactly
what you mean.

394
00:22:05,699 --> 00:22:07,700
My favorite bird
is the spotted owl.

395
00:22:07,784 --> 00:22:09,577
I’ve always
been mesmerized

396
00:22:09,661 --> 00:22:11,162
by those big. . .

397
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:14,290
round, intelligent eyes.

398
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:16,250
(LAUGHING LOUDLY)

399
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:17,335
(SCREAMS)

400
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:18,669
Chicken hearts?

401
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:23,841
Chicken hearts!
Oh, gosh.

402
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:25,259
(EXCLAIMS)

403
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:27,762
Oh. . .

404
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:30,431
(ROOSTER CROWING)

405
00:22:32,642 --> 00:22:33,768
Oh.

406
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:36,395
Hello?

407
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:43,611
(CHATTER ON POLICE RADIO)

408
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:52,787
(SOBBING)

409
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:56,749
Oh, Blu.

410
00:22:56,917 --> 00:23:00,252
We should have never
left Moose Lake.

411
00:23:00,504 --> 00:23:02,380
This is all my fault.

412
00:23:02,464 --> 00:23:04,715
No, no, Linda,
Linda, please.

413
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,801
This is not your fault.

414
00:23:08,095 --> 00:23:09,845
You're right.

415
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:12,056
it’s not my fault.

416
00:23:12,349 --> 00:23:13,808
it’s your fault!
What?

417
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:15,559
With your little
bird talk.

418
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:18,312
And that whole
"save the species."

419
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,480
Well, you know what?

420
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,982
Squawk, squawkity,
squawk, squawk!

421
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:24,985
(GASPING) I’m sorry.
l didn't mean to curse.

422
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:26,320
l don't understand.

423
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:28,489
Sylvio is the best guard
in the business.

424
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:29,824
POLICEMAN: So, let me
get this straight.

425
00:23:29,991 --> 00:23:32,118
You were attacked
by a little white bird?

426
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:34,370
Yes, with this rag.

427
00:23:34,538 --> 00:23:36,831
He held it to my
mouth like this.

428
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:39,208
(MUMBLING)

429
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:42,503
(SNIFFING)

430
00:23:44,339 --> 00:23:45,673
We're doomed.

431
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:55,433
Okay. There's no
place like home,

432
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:56,976
there's no place
like home.

433
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,686
How l wish l was
back in my own cage

434
00:23:58,770 --> 00:24:01,856
with my mirror and my swing,
and my little bell.

435
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:03,524
How l miss
my little bell.

436
00:24:04,025 --> 00:24:05,025
(SHUSHING) Play dead.

437
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:07,695
What? l don't need
to play dead,

438
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:08,863
I’m about to have
a heart attack.

439
00:24:08,947 --> 00:24:10,364
Just do it!

440
00:24:10,866 --> 00:24:11,991
Fine.

441
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:14,076
(DRAMATIC GROAN)

442
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,580
(TWITCHING)

443
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:18,664
Stop twitching.

444
00:24:18,832 --> 00:24:21,000
Come on, it's the
twitching that sells it.

445
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:22,460
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

446
00:24:25,464 --> 00:24:27,173
Come on in, kid.

447
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:36,390
Well, what do you know?

448
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,058
Good work, Fernando.

449
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:40,561
You see, boys?

450
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:42,855
What did l tell you
about this one?

451
00:24:43,523 --> 00:24:45,941
That you were going
to pay him half as
much as you said?

452
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,443
No, you idiot.

453
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:50,571
That he reminds me
of myself when
l was that age.

454
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:52,907
Smart, resourceful.

455
00:24:53,074 --> 00:24:54,074
Here you go, kid.

456
00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:57,953
Hey. This is only half
of what you promised me.

457
00:24:58,413 --> 00:24:59,622
Ah, shut up, kid.

458
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:00,956
What the. . .

459
00:25:03,251 --> 00:25:06,337
l thought l told you
l needed these birds alive.

460
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:07,713
Tell me, Fernando. . .

461
00:25:07,881 --> 00:25:09,798
does this look
alive to you?

462
00:25:11,885 --> 00:25:12,885
(EXCLAIMING)

463
00:25:12,969 --> 00:25:13,511
Get her!

464
00:25:13,762 --> 00:25:14,762
Come over here!

465
00:25:15,764 --> 00:25:16,263
Jewel !

466
00:25:18,058 --> 00:25:19,016
Come here!

467
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:20,351
(PANTING)

468
00:25:26,107 --> 00:25:27,149
