469
00:25:27,817 --> 00:25:29,109
pretty bird.

470
00:25:29,528 --> 00:25:30,778
What's the matter?

471
00:25:30,904 --> 00:25:32,154
Cockatoo got your throat?

472
00:25:32,239 --> 00:25:33,239
MARCEL: Nigel !

473
00:25:33,823 --> 00:25:35,741
Alive.

474
00:25:36,243 --> 00:25:37,826
To be continued.

475
00:25:41,957 --> 00:25:42,998
(GROANING)

476
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:46,835
That was your plan?
To take off and leave me?
Gee, thanks.

477
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,879
Well, why didn't
you follow me?

478
00:25:48,964 --> 00:25:50,297
Uh. . .

479
00:25:51,007 --> 00:25:52,633
Nice work, Nigel.

480
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:54,635
Yeah, nice work, Nigel.

481
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:57,763
The last blue macaws
on earth.

482
00:25:58,098 --> 00:25:59,765
These are worth a fortune.

483
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:03,269
Hey, Fernando,
hang these up
in the other room.

484
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:12,903
(BIRDS CALLING)

485
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:17,992
BIRD 1 : Hey, birdie!

486
00:26:18,201 --> 00:26:20,869
Let me out! Let me out!
Let me out of here!

487
00:26:20,954 --> 00:26:22,079
BIRD 2:
Who's a pretty bird?
I’m a pretty bird.

488
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:24,748
Pretty bird,
I’m a pretty bird.
I’m a pretty bird.

489
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,209
l was framed.
They got the wrong guy.

490
00:26:27,544 --> 00:26:29,378
Sorry, guys.
Nothing personal.

491
00:26:40,557 --> 00:26:42,349
So, what's going
to happen to them?

492
00:26:42,434 --> 00:26:45,936
Don't worry,
we're going to find
good homes for them.

493
00:26:46,896 --> 00:26:47,896
Now go home
to your mama.

494
00:26:48,064 --> 00:26:49,273
But l don't have a mama.

495
00:26:49,357 --> 00:26:50,399
Father?

496
00:26:50,483 --> 00:26:52,192
Brother?
Goldfish?

497
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,237
Can we keep him, boss?

498
00:26:56,072 --> 00:26:57,156
No.

499
00:26:58,533 --> 00:27:01,452
TIPA: So, Marcel,
what's really going to
happen to those birds?

500
00:27:01,828 --> 00:27:03,954
Plucked, stuffed,
eaten, who cares?

501
00:27:04,122 --> 00:27:07,625
All l know is
we're going to be rich.
(ALL LAUGHING)

502
00:27:07,709 --> 00:27:09,376
ARMANDO: We're gonna be rich !

503
00:27:57,258 --> 00:27:59,510
Come on, come on !
The game is starting !

504
00:27:59,594 --> 00:28:03,097
Yes, you were very clear.
Tomorrow or the deal is off.

505
00:28:03,264 --> 00:28:05,349
Of course l have
both the macaws.

506
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:08,060
Yes, l will deliver
them myself.

507
00:28:08,144 --> 00:28:09,436
(BIDDING FAREWELL IN FRENCH)

508
00:28:10,563 --> 00:28:12,106
All right, you two. . .

509
00:28:12,273 --> 00:28:13,357
you load the truck tonight.

510
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:14,692
And first thing
in the morning,

511
00:28:14,776 --> 00:28:16,276
we bring those birds
to the airport.

512
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:17,569
You got it?

513
00:28:17,737 --> 00:28:19,571
Yeah, sure.
All right. Heard you.

514
00:28:19,739 --> 00:28:22,074
And one of you,
feed Nigel.

515
00:28:27,622 --> 00:28:28,747
(BOTH GULPING)

516
00:28:28,832 --> 00:28:30,749
Rock, paper,
scissors, shoot!

517
00:28:30,917 --> 00:28:31,750
Yes!

518
00:28:31,835 --> 00:28:34,211
Nuh-uh,
scissors cuts rock.

519
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:36,714
Oh, man. How come
you always win?

520
00:28:40,593 --> 00:28:42,136
Nice birdie.

521
00:28:44,222 --> 00:28:45,305
(WHIMPERING)

522
00:28:46,057 --> 00:28:47,057
Here you go.

523
00:28:47,475 --> 00:28:48,475
(EXCLAIMS)

524
00:28:48,768 --> 00:28:49,768
(GASPS)

