00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:01,739
Okay, pull it together.
The key is not to panic.

528
00:29:01,823 --> 00:29:02,906
I’m not panicking.

529
00:29:02,991 --> 00:29:04,908
l wasn't talking to you,
l was talking to me.

530
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:07,995
But it's okay,
because any minute now,
Linda will find us.

531
00:29:08,079 --> 00:29:11,290
Great. And then
she'll stick us behind
another set of bars, right?

532
00:29:11,374 --> 00:29:12,708
Yeah. l mean, no.

533
00:29:12,792 --> 00:29:15,002
Look, pet, cages
might work for you,

534
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:17,296
but l don't want
to belong to anyone.

535
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:18,464
(RATTLING)

536
00:29:18,548 --> 00:29:19,548
(ALL GASPING)

537
00:29:23,928 --> 00:29:24,928
(SMACKING BEAK)

538
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:28,432
Something seems to be
lodged in my beak.

539
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:30,476
Would you mind?

540
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:32,561
(WHIMPERING)

541
00:29:39,944 --> 00:29:41,403
(CACKLING)

542
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:47,159
l know I’m not
a pretty birdie. . .

543
00:29:47,243 --> 00:29:49,578
but l used to be
quite a looker.

544
00:29:50,038 --> 00:29:51,622
A star.

545
00:29:53,374 --> 00:29:56,335
Lights, camera, action.

546
00:29:56,503 --> 00:29:59,713
l was striking,
suave, ambitious.

547
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:00,839
Feet to beak...

548
00:30:01,216 --> 00:30:02,341
so birdie-licious

549
00:30:02,592 --> 00:30:05,135
Now I'm vile,
I am villainous,
and vicious

550
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:07,012
Oh, and malicious

551
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:09,640
l had it all
A TV show, women, too

552
00:30:09,724 --> 00:30:12,434
l was tall
Over one-foot-two

553
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:15,145
Then they got a
pretty parakeet
to fill my shoes

554
00:30:15,313 --> 00:30:17,523
That's why l am so evil,
why l do what l do.

555
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:18,690
CHORUS: He was a super star

556
00:30:18,775 --> 00:30:20,067
So young and vital

557
00:30:20,151 --> 00:30:21,235
He's nasty

558
00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:22,736
A South American Idol

559
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:24,029
He's a suspicious bird

560
00:30:24,113 --> 00:30:25,280
Who said that about me?

561
00:30:25,365 --> 00:30:27,866
A very vicious bird
I’ll have you rotisseried

562
00:30:27,951 --> 00:30:29,660
I’m a feathery freak
With a beak

563
00:30:29,744 --> 00:30:30,911
A bird murderer

564
00:30:30,995 --> 00:30:33,539
You think you're
badder than me?
l never heard of ya

565
00:30:33,623 --> 00:30:36,166
I'm evil,
I’ll fill your cheese balls
with weevils

566
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:38,710
l poop on people
and l blame it on seagulls

567
00:30:39,796 --> 00:30:40,879
(WHISPERING)
It was him.

568
00:30:41,297 --> 00:30:43,465
He's a nasty bird
I’m invincible

569
00:30:43,633 --> 00:30:46,009
He's ghastly
I’m un-mince-able

570
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:48,512
I'm unwashable, unrinseable

571
00:30:48,596 --> 00:30:51,098
Like an abandoned school
l have no principle

572
00:30:51,266 --> 00:30:53,559
All of you Brazilian birds

573
00:30:53,643 --> 00:30:55,978
All 80 million birds

574
00:30:56,062 --> 00:30:58,438
I’ll tell you what
I’m going to do

575
00:30:58,523 --> 00:31:00,190
I’m going to make you

576
00:31:00,275 --> 00:31:01,358
(BIRDS VOCALIZING)

577
00:31:01,442 --> 00:31:02,985
Shut up, now. Shut up!

578
00:31:03,069 --> 00:31:04,069
(SILENCE)

579
00:31:04,153 --> 00:31:05,320
it’s just me.

580
00:31:05,488 --> 00:31:09,449
l will make you ugly...

581
00:31:10,201 --> 00:31:11,410
...too.

582
00:31:11,494 --> 00:31:12,494
BLU: Hey!

583
00:31:12,579 --> 00:31:13,620
Sweet nightmares.

584
00:31:13,705 --> 00:31:15,163
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

585
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:17,749
Not cool, man !

586
00:31:17,834 --> 00:31:19,710
Scary, but not cool !

587
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:21,587
Hey, are you okay?

588
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:24,381
No, l am definitely
not okay!

589
00:31:24,465 --> 00:31:25,716
Wait. What are
you doing?

590
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,426
Getting out of here.

591
00:31:27,510 --> 00:31:28,969
Are you going to
help me or what?

592
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:30,637
Actually, all the
survival guides

593
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:32,806
say to sit and wait,
and help will come.

594
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:34,308
No one is coming !

595
00:31:34,392 --> 00:31:37,895
We are on our own
and if we just sit here,
we're going to die!

596
00:31:37,979 --> 00:31:39,146
(METAL CLANKING)

597
00:31:39,772 --> 00:31:41,565
Yes! Yes!

598
00:31:41,983 --> 00:31:42,649
Yes!

599
00:31:43,151 --> 00:31:44,318
No!

600
00:31:44,485 --> 00:31:46,820
ARMANDO: Nigel !
Get out of the way!

601
00:31:47,572 --> 00:31:48,572
Hold on !

602
00:31:49,032 --> 00:31:52,242
Stop! Stop!
Why don't you just
open the door?

603
00:31:52,785 --> 00:31:53,869
Are you kidding me?

604
00:31:53,953 --> 00:31:55,704
What? it’s just
a standard
flip slide bolt.

605
00:31:55,788 --> 00:31:56,830
Come on ! Let's fly!

606
00:31:57,624 --> 00:31:58,707
What are you doing?

607
00:31:58,791 --> 00:32:00,709
l can't.
What? You can't what?

608
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:03,170
(BLU GASPS)

609
00:32:05,465 --> 00:32:08,091
l can't fly!
(JEWEL SCREAMING)

610
00:32:09,302 --> 00:32:11,261
You couldn't tell me
this before now?

611
00:32:11,346 --> 00:32:13,138
It didn't matter
before now!

612
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:18,101
l hate you.

613
00:32:18,186 --> 00:32:19,353
(SCREAMING)

614
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:22,564
Is there anything else
l need to know?

615
00:32:22,649 --> 00:32:24,358
Yes, l can't fly,
l pick my beak,

616
00:32:24,442 --> 00:32:25,567
and once in a while
l pee in the bird-bath.

617
00:32:25,652 --> 00:32:26,652
Happy?

618
00:32:26,778 --> 00:32:27,778
There they are!

619
00:32:27,862 --> 00:32:28,862
We got to get
out of here!

620
00:32:29,113 --> 00:32:30,364
Just move! Move!

621
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:34,159
Wait, wait.
Listen to me.

622
00:32:34,327 --> 00:32:36,370
Flying may not
be my thing,
but walking is.

623
00:32:36,454 --> 00:32:38,288
Follow my lead.
Inside leg, outside leg.

624
00:32:38,373 --> 00:32:39,373
Yeah, okay,
l got it.

625
00:32:39,457 --> 00:32:42,000
Inside, outside,
inside, outside!

626
00:32:42,168 --> 00:32:45,504
(CHANTING)
Yes! Yes! Yes!

627
00:32:45,672 --> 00:32:47,798
Yes. Yes!
Come on !

628
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:53,220
(MIMICKING DOG)

629
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:55,722
(CAT SCREECHING)

630
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:58,392
See? I’m bilingual, too!

631
00:32:59,769 --> 00:33:01,061
(NIGEL SQUAWKING HARSHLY)

632
00:33:03,189 --> 00:33:04,189
This is great!

633
00:33:04,273 --> 00:33:06,400
I’m chained to the
only bird in the world
who can't fly!

634
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:08,902
Actually, there are
about 40 species
of flightless birds.

635
00:33:08,987 --> 00:33:10,362
Duck!
No, ducks can fly.

636
00:33:10,446 --> 00:33:11,780
No! Duck!

637
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:16,535
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

638
00:33:19,414 --> 00:33:21,248
(EXCLAIMING)
Yay!

639
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:23,959
(BOTH SCREAMING)

640
00:33:33,177 --> 00:33:34,011
ALL: Yes!

641
00:33:34,095 --> 00:33:35,262
(COMMENTATOR
SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

642
00:33:36,472 --> 00:33:45,522
Yes!

643
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:46,857
Hold on !

644
00:33:47,692 --> 00:33:48,400
NIGEL: No!

645
00:33:49,485 --> 00:33:50,485
No!

646
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:53,405
ALL: No!

647
00:33:56,284 --> 00:33:58,952
(CLUCKING)

648
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,620
(NIGEL GROANING)

649
00:34:02,957 --> 00:34:05,500
Get out of here,
you putrid poultry!

650
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:10,547
(EXCLAIMING)

651
00:34:17,972 --> 00:34:19,806
(CHAIN CLINKING)

652
00:34:22,477 --> 00:34:23,477
(TWIG SNAPPING)

653
00:34:23,561 --> 00:34:24,561
What was that?

654
00:34:24,645 --> 00:34:25,687
A stick.

655
00:34:25,772 --> 00:34:26,772
And that?

656
00:34:26,856 --> 00:34:28,023
it’s just a rock.

657
00:34:28,107 --> 00:34:29,566
Right. Yeah.

658
00:34:30,401 --> 00:34:31,818
(SHUDDERING)

659
00:34:31,903 --> 00:34:33,153
Is that a spider
on my back?

660
00:34:33,237 --> 00:34:34,780
Will you quit it?

661
00:34:34,864 --> 00:34:37,115
it’s just a leaf.
Turn around.

662
00:34:41,788 --> 00:34:43,580
Leaf. Told you.

663
00:34:44,457 --> 00:34:47,334
Now, come on, we need
to find a safe place
to spend the night.

664
00:34:47,418 --> 00:34:48,543
Safe? Safe?

665
00:34:48,711 --> 00:34:50,003
We are in the jungle.

666
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:52,047
You know when people say,
"it’s a jungle out there"?

667
00:34:52,131 --> 00:34:53,965
Well, I’m pretty sure
they don't mean it
as a good thing.

668
00:34:54,050 --> 00:34:55,675
Look, l hate to
break it to you,

669
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:58,053
but this is where our
kind naturally lives.

670
00:34:58,137 --> 00:34:59,846
Hey, don't talk
to me about nature.

671
00:34:59,931 --> 00:35:01,556
I watch Animal Planet.

672
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:03,809
l know all about
the food chain.

673
00:35:06,479 --> 00:35:09,481
(EXCLAIMING) You see?
Out here, I’m just an
hors d'oeuvre.

674
00:35:09,565 --> 00:35:11,608
Nothing more than
a feathery spring roll.

675
00:35:11,692 --> 00:35:14,945
That is why we stay
in the trees and
not on the ground.

676
00:35:15,029 --> 00:35:16,321
After you.

677
00:35:17,907 --> 00:35:19,074
(MOANING) No,
l don't think so.

678
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:21,368
Nuh-uh. No.
l would feel much
more comfortable

679
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:23,620
in something man-made.

680
00:35:25,081 --> 00:35:27,040
Hey, how about
up there?

681
00:35:29,794 --> 00:35:33,213
l can't believe
l have to drag your
clumsy butt up there.

682
00:35:33,756 --> 00:35:34,756
Drag me? (SCOFFS)

683
00:35:34,841 --> 00:35:36,341
Watch and learn.

684
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:37,717
Oh !

685
00:35:39,053 --> 00:35:41,221
Blu ! Just wait one. . .

686
00:35:41,514 --> 00:35:42,514
Blu?

687
00:35:43,307 --> 00:35:45,433
Who's dragging
whose butt now?

688
00:35:46,060 --> 00:35:47,394
Ha ha. Very funny.

689
00:35:48,521 --> 00:35:49,729
(LAUGHING)

690
00:35:55,111 --> 00:35:56,695
You see?
Who needs flying?

691
00:35:56,779 --> 00:35:59,322
Birds. Birds
need flying.

692
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:00,740
Flying is. . .

693
00:36:01,909 --> 00:36:05,162
it’s freedom
and not having
to rely on anyone.

694
00:36:06,622 --> 00:36:08,415
Don't you want that?

695
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:11,626
l don't know.
It sounds a little lonely.

696
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:14,004
Let's get some sleep.

697
00:36:15,506 --> 00:36:18,133
I’m probably
going to be up
for a little while.

698
00:36:18,217 --> 00:36:20,552
Because I’m still
on Minnesota time.

699
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:22,220
Good night.

700
00:36:23,097 --> 00:36:24,556
Good night, Jewel.

701
00:36:28,019 --> 00:36:29,936
Good night, Linda.

702
00:36:36,944 --> 00:36:38,570
Excuse me, sir?

703
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:43,200
Have you seen my bird?

704
00:36:43,284 --> 00:36:44,367
Mmm-mmm.

705
00:36:44,452 --> 00:36:45,577
(SIGHING)

706
00:36:46,829 --> 00:36:49,289
Excuse me?
Have you seen my bird?

707
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:22,822
(SNORING)

708
00:37:24,492 --> 00:37:28,245
(MUMBLING) Have you
seen my bird?
Blue feather.

709
00:37:28,329 --> 00:37:30,038
Lady! American lady!

710
00:37:30,122 --> 00:37:31,248
(GASPS)

711
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:32,749
Blu?
Where?

712
00:37:32,833 --> 00:37:34,125
(EXCLAIMING)

713
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:35,961
(GASPS)

714
00:37:36,045 --> 00:37:38,505
Wow. l know where
your birds are.

715
00:37:38,589 --> 00:37:40,799
You found Blu?
Are you sure?

716
00:37:41,676 --> 00:37:42,676
(GASPING) it’s his!

717
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:43,969
Let me see that.

718
00:37:46,097 --> 00:37:47,639
(VOCALIZING)

719
00:37:50,142 --> 00:37:51,101
You're right.

720
00:37:51,269 --> 00:37:52,852
Okay. Where is he?

721
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:55,313
Come on, let's go!
I’ll take you to him.

722
00:37:55,398 --> 00:37:57,274
No, no. Linda, wait.

723
00:37:57,441 --> 00:38:00,777
We don't know this boy.
We can't trust him.

724
00:38:03,406 --> 00:38:06,074
l have to trust him.

725
00:38:06,242 --> 00:38:08,702
l don't have a choice.

726
00:38:09,203 --> 00:38:11,037
(CLUCKING)

727
00:38:18,546 --> 00:38:19,754
(CLEARING THROAT)

728
00:38:21,424 --> 00:38:23,800
Do you think
I’m an idiot?

729
00:38:25,386 --> 00:38:29,264
They were two birds
chained together in a cage.

730
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:30,682
How could you lose them?

731
00:38:30,766 --> 00:38:32,809
They outsmarted us, boss.

732
00:38:32,893 --> 00:38:34,561
But don't worry,
we'll get them back.

733
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:36,396
l have a plan.

734
00:38:36,564 --> 00:38:38,398
Great. What are
you going to do?

735
00:38:38,482 --> 00:38:42,235
Wander the city
calling "Here birdie,
birdie. Here birdie"?

736
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:45,405
Well, anything sounds dumb
when you say it like that.

737
00:38:45,489 --> 00:38:46,531
(SNICKERING)

738
00:38:46,615 --> 00:38:49,409
Okay. We have
to get the birds to
the airport tonight.

739
00:38:49,618 --> 00:38:52,495
But it's Carnaval.
All the roads will be
blocked by the parade.

740
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:55,832
And that's why
l wanted to go
this morning.

741
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:57,250
Nigel.

742
00:38:57,626 --> 00:39:01,087
This bird is 1 0 times
smarter than the two
of you combined.

743
00:39:01,255 --> 00:39:03,340
Yeah, well,
if he's so smart,

744
00:39:03,424 --> 00:39:04,758
then why don't you
put him in charge?

745
00:39:05,092 --> 00:39:06,801
l am putting
him in charge.

746
00:39:08,554 --> 00:39:10,597
Stop suggesting things.

747
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:12,766
Go find them, Nigel.

748
00:39:16,479 --> 00:39:18,104
(KIDS CHEERING)

749
00:39:20,941 --> 00:39:21,983
Hmm.

750
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,361
lf we can't get
through the parade,

751
00:39:24,445 --> 00:39:26,321
we'll have to be
in the parade.

752
00:39:26,405 --> 00:39:27,405
Huh?

753
00:39:28,449 --> 00:39:29,949
(GRUNTING)

754
00:39:31,202 --> 00:39:33,244
JEWEL: Are you sure
this is going to work?

755
00:39:33,621 --> 00:39:35,705
Positive.
Check out my math.

756
00:39:36,499 --> 00:39:39,626
Yeah, that's comforting.
Thank you.

757
00:39:39,752 --> 00:39:42,128
Look, let's just get
this chain broken.

758
00:39:42,338 --> 00:39:44,381
Right. Then we can
go and find Linda.

759
00:39:44,673 --> 00:39:46,758
No, you can
go find Linda.

760
00:39:46,926 --> 00:39:48,343
Once this chain is off,

761
00:39:48,427 --> 00:39:50,637
I’m going to go back
to being free in the
jungle. Deal?

762
00:39:50,721 --> 00:39:51,763
Fine. Deal.

763
00:39:59,438 --> 00:40:01,439
Nice try, brainiac.

764
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:03,858
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

765
00:40:04,985 --> 00:40:06,444
l think something
is watching us.

766
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:09,155
(CHEEPING)

767
00:40:12,326 --> 00:40:15,286
Be careful, Blu.
They might snuggle
you to death.

768
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:19,124
Come here.

769
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:21,501
Ow!

770
00:40:23,879 --> 00:40:25,046
Intruders!

771
00:40:25,381 --> 00:40:27,132
Cut it out!

772
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:30,802
Now stop. . .

773
00:40:30,886 --> 00:40:31,886
(SCREAMING)

774
00:40:33,305 --> 00:40:35,306
No! Don't!

775
00:40:37,685 --> 00:40:38,685
Attack!

776
00:40:39,979 --> 00:40:40,979
(BOTH SCREAMING)

777
00:40:41,063 --> 00:40:42,105
BLU: Help!

778
00:40:42,189 --> 00:40:43,773
What's going on
down there?

779
00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:47,110
Go, go. Off with you.

780
00:40:47,194 --> 00:40:48,278
Daddy! Daddy! Daddy!

781
00:40:48,404 --> 00:40:49,946
I’ve told you
a thousand times.

782
00:40:50,030 --> 00:40:51,781
Manoela, Sofia,
come on now, listen to me.

783
00:40:51,866 --> 00:40:53,032
Oh, yeah,
right in the eye.

784
00:40:53,826 --> 00:40:55,201
Precious, aren't they?

785
00:40:55,536 --> 00:40:58,037
Kids? Seventeen of them
and one on the way.

786
00:40:58,164 --> 00:41:01,207
Hey! He's not a maraca,
stop shaking him !

787
00:41:03,586 --> 00:41:06,004
They're giving me
gray feathers.

788
00:41:06,172 --> 00:41:08,381
(MOANING)
This papa needs a break.

789
00:41:08,549 --> 00:41:10,884
So, you two lovebirds
headed for Carnaval?

790
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:12,343
Whoa! Lovebirds?

791
00:41:12,428 --> 00:41:13,720
We're more like
acquaintance-birds.

792
00:41:13,804 --> 00:41:16,347
Not even that,
we're more like chained-
to-each-other birds.

793
00:41:16,432 --> 00:41:18,057
Yeah. l mean, if. . . Ow!

794
00:41:19,518 --> 00:41:20,935
What is it with this kid
and the feathers?

795
00:41:21,061 --> 00:41:23,730
We have no idea.
We're having him tested.

796
00:41:23,898 --> 00:41:27,942
So, do you think
you could help us
get this thing off?

797
00:41:29,403 --> 00:41:31,988
Lucky for you,
you know Rafael,

798
00:41:32,072 --> 00:41:34,199
and Rafael knows everyone.

799
00:41:34,742 --> 00:41:36,951
Again with the eye.
Okay, want me
to call your mother?

800
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:38,369
KIDS: No!

801
00:41:38,454 --> 00:41:40,538
Works every time.
They're scared
to death of her.

802
00:41:40,623 --> 00:41:42,582
Call me for what?

803
00:41:42,750 --> 00:41:43,875
Eva, my love. . .

804
00:41:44,376 --> 00:41:46,544
l must take
this young couple
to see Luiz.

805
00:41:46,629 --> 00:41:47,837
Luiz!

806
00:41:47,922 --> 00:41:50,131
You don't fool me
for a second.

807
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:53,259
You and your amigo
just want to sneak off
to Carnaval.

808
00:41:54,428 --> 00:41:55,762
Carnaval.

809
00:41:55,930 --> 00:42:00,433
That magical time when
l met the most beautiful
bird in the world.

810
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:01,935
Oh !
Ugh.

811
00:42:02,728 --> 00:42:07,148
l still remember the song
that was playing when
l first laid eyes on you.

812
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:10,944
Tall and tan and
young and lovely

813
00:42:11,028 --> 00:42:14,864
The girl from Ipanema
goes walking

814
00:42:14,949 --> 00:42:15,949
Come on, baby, sing it!

815
00:42:16,158 --> 00:42:20,078
(OFF-KEY)
And when she passes,
each one she passes goes, ah!

816
00:42:20,746 --> 00:42:22,163
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

817
00:42:22,998 --> 00:42:25,208
Like a river of
the sweetest honey.

818
00:42:25,501 --> 00:42:28,002
Oh. l guess
love is deaf, too.

819
00:42:28,170 --> 00:42:29,546
Come here.

820
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:30,922
ALL: Eww.

821
00:42:32,883 --> 00:42:37,136
Okay. Take them to Luiz,
but hurry back.

822
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:38,805
You are an angel.

823
00:42:38,973 --> 00:42:40,932
I’ll miss you
my juicy little mango.

824
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:42,934
I’ll miss you
my pudgy papaya.

825
00:42:43,018 --> 00:42:44,185
(KIDS SHOUTING)

826
00:42:44,436 --> 00:42:47,814
Hey! Marco! Carlos!
Put your brother down, now!

827
00:42:47,982 --> 00:42:49,816
l can't believe
she actually let me go.

828
00:42:49,942 --> 00:42:52,026
So, how far
is this Luiz?

829
00:42:52,194 --> 00:42:55,530
Not far. Thirty minutes
as the crow flies.

830
00:42:55,698 --> 00:42:57,740
And how long as
the macaw walks?

831
00:42:57,825 --> 00:42:59,242
Bobo here can't fly.

832
00:42:59,326 --> 00:43:00,410
But he's a bird.

833
00:43:00,494 --> 00:43:01,327
Not all birds fly.

834
00:43:01,495 --> 00:43:02,203
There are ostriches. . .

835
00:43:02,538 --> 00:43:03,538
You're not an ostrich.

836
00:43:03,664 --> 00:43:05,164
Not technically, but. . .
Wait.

837
00:43:05,291 --> 00:43:07,709
My friends, l want to help,
but to walk the whole way. . .

838
00:43:07,835 --> 00:43:08,835
It can't be done!

839
00:43:08,919 --> 00:43:09,919
KID: Where's Daddy?

840
00:43:10,004 --> 00:43:11,921
Daddy? Daddy?
Come over here.
Go back to your room.

841
00:43:12,006 --> 00:43:13,047
But, hey.

842
00:43:13,173 --> 00:43:15,091
We might as well
give it a shot.
Let's go quickly.

843
00:43:15,175 --> 00:43:17,510
No, don't look back.
They sense fear.

844
00:43:41,827 --> 00:43:43,494
(SCREECHING)

845
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:45,163
What an adorable monkey.

846
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:49,417
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

847
00:43:55,966 --> 00:43:56,966
(CALLING)

848
00:43:59,053 --> 00:44:00,386
(BLOWING RASPBERRY)

849
00:44:02,514 --> 00:44:03,723
Hey! My watch !

850
00:44:30,084 --> 00:44:31,292
Hello, boys.

851
00:44:31,418 --> 00:44:33,878
Seems like you've
had a busy day.

852
00:44:34,046 --> 00:44:35,129
What? This?

853
00:44:35,297 --> 00:44:37,840
This is just some
stuff we found.

854
00:44:37,925 --> 00:44:39,092
Right, boys?

855
00:44:39,218 --> 00:44:40,510
Yeah.
Yeah.

856
00:44:40,594 --> 00:44:43,012
I’m not interested
in your nicked knick-knacks.

857
00:44:43,097 --> 00:44:45,932
Your burgled baubles bore me.

858
00:44:46,058 --> 00:44:48,518
There are two blue
macaws out there

859
00:44:48,602 --> 00:44:52,438
and l need your
multitude of eyes
to help me find them.

860
00:44:52,564 --> 00:44:55,316
Oh, yeah?
What's in it for us?

861
00:44:55,901 --> 00:44:57,443
Well, that's
a fair question.

862
00:44:59,905 --> 00:45:01,030
(SCREAMING)

863
00:45:02,783 --> 00:45:04,242
Let's discuss it.

864
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:08,788
l certainly
see your point,

865
00:45:08,872 --> 00:45:11,791
but what could l possibly
do for you in return?

866
00:45:11,959 --> 00:45:13,835
Save me! Save me!

867
00:45:14,253 --> 00:45:16,129
Well, that's
a thought. Yeah.

868
00:45:16,255 --> 00:45:18,798
But is it enough?
l don't want to feel
like I’m cheating you.

869
00:45:18,924 --> 00:45:20,383
Help me!
Help me! No, no!

870
00:45:20,467 --> 00:45:22,677
We'll do it, we'll do it.
Save me, please.

871
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:25,304
Save me!

872
00:45:27,349 --> 00:45:28,975
All right,
you've twisted my wing.

873
00:45:29,143 --> 00:45:30,560
Deal.

874
00:45:30,686 --> 00:45:33,146
Now then?
Any more questions?

875
00:45:33,814 --> 00:45:35,314
No? Good.

876
00:45:35,482 --> 00:45:38,109
You will spread out and
you will find these macaws

877
00:45:38,193 --> 00:45:39,402
by the end of the day

878
00:45:39,486 --> 00:45:41,654
or it's flying lessons
for everyone!

879
00:45:41,864 --> 00:45:43,072
Go!

880
00:45:43,157 --> 00:45:44,657
(ALL HOOTING)

881
00:45:45,659 --> 00:45:48,077
Go do your
monkey business.

882
00:45:57,838 --> 00:45:59,338
(WHIMPERING)

883
00:46:03,177 --> 00:46:05,511
(PANTING) I’ve changed
my mind, yeah.

884
00:46:05,846 --> 00:46:08,181
Maybe we can find
a bus schedule
or something.

885
00:46:08,307 --> 00:46:10,183
Come on, you're not
going to back out now.

886
00:46:10,517 --> 00:46:12,518
Not in front of the lady.

887
00:46:14,396 --> 00:46:16,189
Okay, yeah.
Yeah, sure.

888
00:46:16,356 --> 00:46:17,899
All right,
that's the spirit.

889
00:46:18,108 --> 00:46:19,525
You're sure
you're up for this?

890
00:46:19,610 --> 00:46:20,943
Yeah, yeah. l mean,

891
00:46:21,028 --> 00:46:22,779
it's not like we're
just hurling ourselves

892
00:46:22,863 --> 00:46:24,614
off a mountain or something.

893
00:46:24,698 --> 00:46:25,698
Right?

894
00:46:25,824 --> 00:46:27,784
Actually that
was pretty much
my entire plan.

895
00:46:27,868 --> 00:46:28,868
What?

896
00:46:28,994 --> 00:46:31,537
Don't worry, Blu,
it's in your DNA.

897
00:46:31,663 --> 00:46:34,040
And if our featherless
friends can do it,
how hard can it be?

898
00:46:34,124 --> 00:46:35,374
MAN: Wait, wait!

899
00:46:35,626 --> 00:46:36,751
(SCREAMING)

900
00:46:37,377 --> 00:46:39,337
Mommy!

901
00:46:39,505 --> 00:46:40,630
Fun, right?

902
00:46:40,714 --> 00:46:42,340
Yeah. Fun.

903
00:46:43,133 --> 00:46:45,510
Okay. l need you
two to get closer.

904
00:46:46,678 --> 00:46:51,265
Closer.

905
00:46:53,185 --> 00:46:54,227
Nice.

906
00:46:54,645 --> 00:46:55,937
Now put your wings
around each other.

907
00:46:56,355 --> 00:46:57,939
What?
Come on, amigo!

908
00:46:58,065 --> 00:46:59,816
it’s not like
she's going to bite!

909
00:46:59,900 --> 00:47:00,900
Will you?

910
00:47:01,068 --> 00:47:02,235
We'll see.

911
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:03,152
Now,

912
00:47:03,237 --> 00:47:04,362
you flap your right wing,

913
00:47:04,446 --> 00:47:08,407
you flap your left wing,
and together you fly.

914
00:47:08,700 --> 00:47:11,702
But this doesn't seem
aerodynamically possible.

915
00:47:12,913 --> 00:47:14,288
(EXCLAIMING)
You think too much.

916
00:47:14,414 --> 00:47:16,499
Flying is not what
you think up here,

917
00:47:16,583 --> 00:47:18,793
it's what
you feel in here.

918
00:47:18,919 --> 00:47:20,711
And when you feel
the rhythm of your heart,

919
00:47:20,796 --> 00:47:22,338
it's like samba.

920
00:47:22,422 --> 00:47:23,923
You fly!

921
00:47:25,050 --> 00:47:26,717
(WHOOPING)

922
00:47:28,887 --> 00:47:30,555
See? it’s easy!

923
00:47:30,722 --> 00:47:31,722
Easy?

924
00:47:31,807 --> 00:47:33,516
Easy for you to say,
because from here

925
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:35,977
it looks really,
really hard.

926
00:47:36,103 --> 00:47:38,437
Hey, if you want
to see Linda again,

927
00:47:38,522 --> 00:47:40,106
this is the only way.

928
00:47:40,399 --> 00:47:41,858
Okay. You're right.

929
00:47:41,942 --> 00:47:43,317
Yes, l am.
This is for Linda.

930
00:47:43,443 --> 00:47:44,527
Right.
Keep it simple.

931
00:47:44,611 --> 00:47:46,988
Easy breezy.
Thrust, lift, drag. . .

932
00:47:47,114 --> 00:47:48,197
Come on ! Let's go!
Wait!

933
00:47:48,282 --> 00:47:50,533
Inside, outside,
inside, outside.

934
00:47:50,617 --> 00:47:51,701
Come on, Blu !
You can do it!

935
00:47:51,785 --> 00:47:52,910
BLU: l can do it.
l can do it.

936
00:47:52,995 --> 00:47:53,578
l can do it.

937
00:47:53,620 --> 00:47:55,204
l can't do it!

938
00:47:55,998 --> 00:47:56,998
Not again !

939
00:47:58,625 --> 00:47:59,917
(BOTH SCREAMING)

940
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:09,427
Am l dead?
No!

941
00:48:09,511 --> 00:48:11,220
We're still alive!

942
00:48:11,305 --> 00:48:12,597
(WHOOPING)

943
00:48:13,849 --> 00:48:15,975
(MAS QUE NADA PLAYING)

944
00:48:21,982 --> 00:48:25,484
Wow! This is incredible.

945
00:48:37,289 --> 00:48:38,289
Wow.

946
00:48:38,373 --> 00:48:41,250
This is the most
beautiful thing
I’ve ever seen.

947
00:48:41,668 --> 00:48:43,294
(LAUGHING)
See what you've
been missing?

948
00:48:43,378 --> 00:48:45,004
Yeah.

949
00:48:50,677 --> 00:48:53,012
All right, Blu,
you're flying !

950
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:56,015
Sort of. Not really,
but do you feel it?

951
00:48:56,266 --> 00:48:57,308
Yes!

952
00:48:58,185 --> 00:48:59,852
l do feel it.

953
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:14,784
No, no, Blu ! Wait!

954
00:49:15,869 --> 00:49:17,286
(EXCLAIMING IN PORTUGUESE)

955
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:19,413
(BOTH SCREAMING)

956
00:49:25,379 --> 00:49:26,420
(SCREAMING)

957
00:49:26,505 --> 00:49:28,047
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

958
00:49:29,299 --> 00:49:30,800
We're gonna die!

959
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:34,720
(ALL SCREAMING)

960
00:49:57,911 --> 00:50:00,538
You did not
feel it in here.

961
00:50:00,706 --> 00:50:01,831
You think?

962
00:50:01,915 --> 00:50:02,915
(TRUCK ENGINE STARING)

963
00:50:04,251 --> 00:50:06,127
Let's catch
a ride to Luiz.

964
00:50:08,922 --> 00:50:09,630
Hurry, you two!

965
00:50:09,715 --> 00:50:11,173
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

966
00:50:11,258 --> 00:50:12,258
Okay.

967
00:50:12,718 --> 00:50:14,427
Last of the species here.

968
00:50:14,970 --> 00:50:16,053
Move it!

969
00:50:16,138 --> 00:50:17,638
Hey. Wait up.

970
00:50:17,764 --> 00:50:18,848
Come on, lovebirds!

971
00:50:21,476 --> 00:50:22,935
You made it.

972
00:50:23,061 --> 00:50:25,771
l would love to go
five minutes without
almost getting killed.

973
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:26,939
Is that too much to ask?

974
00:50:27,065 --> 00:50:29,900
For a bird who
can't fly, oh, yeah.

975
00:50:31,778 --> 00:50:32,778
(WHISTLING)

976
00:50:35,365 --> 00:50:37,450
TULIO: They're starting
to close off the
streets for Carnaval.

977
00:50:37,951 --> 00:50:41,412
You better be right, kid.
Because we're
running out of time.

978
00:50:44,332 --> 00:50:45,875
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

979
00:50:50,130 --> 00:50:51,464
(HONKING)

980
00:50:53,383 --> 00:50:55,426
(GROANING) I’ll never
be able to get my car
through this crowd.

981
00:50:55,761 --> 00:50:57,136
Don't worry,
I’m on it.

982
00:50:59,306 --> 00:51:00,306
(EXCLAIMING)

983
00:51:00,932 --> 00:51:02,141
Watch it!

984
00:51:02,976 --> 00:51:04,602
Hey, kid, how did
you get this bike?

985
00:51:04,686 --> 00:51:06,896
l traded it for your Jeep.
What?

986
00:51:07,022 --> 00:51:09,315
Yeah, it's in
great condition.

987
00:51:10,484 --> 00:51:12,443
Well, good condition !

988
00:51:13,403 --> 00:51:14,487
Hey! Out of the way!

989
00:51:15,155 --> 00:51:16,155
Look out!

990
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:19,658
FERNANDO: Hold on !

991
00:51:32,714 --> 00:51:33,923
(EXCLAIMING) Ow!

992
00:51:34,007 --> 00:51:35,466
I’m going to chew
through my own leg

993
00:51:35,550 --> 00:51:36,759
if this doesn't
come off soon.

994
00:51:36,843 --> 00:51:39,595
Relax. lf l know Luiz,
we're right where
we want to be.

995
00:51:39,679 --> 00:51:41,013
NICO: Hey! Rafi !

996
00:51:41,223 --> 00:51:43,682
lf it isn't the king
of Carnaval !

997
00:51:43,850 --> 00:51:46,018
Nico! Pedro!
What up, family?

998
00:51:46,186 --> 00:51:47,853
Where you been
hiding yourself, bird?

999
00:51:47,938 --> 00:51:49,188
Man, l thought
you were dead.

1000
00:51:49,314 --> 00:51:51,190
Hold up! Rewind.

1001
00:51:51,858 --> 00:51:53,526
Ain't that the bird
from the cage?

1002
00:51:53,652 --> 00:51:56,028
l think our love lessons
went down smooth.

1003
00:51:56,196 --> 00:51:57,363
You work fast.

1004
00:51:57,447 --> 00:51:58,572
Baby got beak.

1005
00:51:58,698 --> 00:52:01,367
You was locked up
and now you're rolling
with a hot-wing.

1006
00:52:01,493 --> 00:52:02,785
(WHOOPS)
l want to be like you.

1007
00:52:02,869 --> 00:52:05,371
No, it's not what you think.
We're just chained together.

1008
00:52:05,455 --> 00:52:06,789
Hey, I’m not judging you.

1009
00:52:06,873 --> 00:52:08,582
Keep it spicy.
Oh, yeah.

1010
00:52:09,251 --> 00:52:10,709
Hey, guys,
we're looking for Luiz.
Have you seen him?

1011
00:52:11,336 --> 00:52:12,378
Yeah, l seen him,
but you didn't,

1012
00:52:12,462 --> 00:52:13,462
because you
just missed him.

1013
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,631
He took the trolley
back to the garage.

1014
00:52:15,715 --> 00:52:16,715
Great.

1015
00:52:16,883 --> 00:52:19,093
Relax, baby bird.
You could catch
the next one.

1016
00:52:19,219 --> 00:52:21,262
Yeah, it's time to take it
to the next level.

1017
00:52:21,680 --> 00:52:22,888
What's wrong
with this level?

1018
00:52:23,014 --> 00:52:25,558
Come on ! This ain't the level.
The next level's the level.

1019
00:52:25,725 --> 00:52:27,184
You got to shake
your tail feathers.

1020
00:52:27,269 --> 00:52:28,978
We got to get
this chain off first.

1021
00:52:29,062 --> 00:52:32,398
Come on, lovebirds!
You're in Rio!
You should enjoy it!

1022
00:52:32,524 --> 00:52:34,733
Yeah ! Live a little.

1023
00:52:39,656 --> 00:52:40,656
(YELPS)

1024
00:52:45,871 --> 00:52:47,913
(VIBRATING)

1025
00:52:48,915 --> 00:52:49,874
(SIGHING)

1026
00:52:49,958 --> 00:52:51,292
(PHONE CHIMES)

1027
00:52:54,588 --> 00:52:55,629
(LAUGHING)

1028
00:52:55,714 --> 00:52:57,423
We got them.

1029
00:52:58,383 --> 00:53:00,426
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)
BIRD: Hey!

1030
00:53:05,807 --> 00:53:08,225
Welcome to paradise!

1031
00:53:08,935 --> 00:53:10,311
Some party, huh?

1032
00:53:10,437 --> 00:53:12,229
This is the coolest place
I’ve ever seen.

1033
00:53:12,314 --> 00:53:15,065
Despite all the obvious
health code violations.

1034
00:53:15,775 --> 00:53:18,819
l like you !
Nothing you say
makes any sense.

1035
00:53:19,946 --> 00:53:21,447
All right, everyone,
listen up!

1036
00:53:21,531 --> 00:53:24,158
Rafi has some special
guests from out of town

1037
00:53:24,284 --> 00:53:25,951
and let's show
them some love,

1038
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:27,870
because l don't think
they get out much.

1039
00:53:27,954 --> 00:53:28,996
